
Extract all financial transactions from the document below.

FIELD DEFINITIONS:
- filing_id      : The unique document ID found on the filing (string)
- first_name     : First name of the filer including e.g. "Nancy Pelosi" (string) -> Nancy
- last_name      : Last name of the filer e.g. "Nancy Pelosi" (string) -> Pelosi
- middle_name    : last_name if applicable
- status         : Filer role — one of: "Member", "Spouse", "Dependent" (string)
- state_district : State and district code e.g. "CA11" (string)

TRANSACTION FIELDS:
- asset_name      : Full legal name of the asset (string)
- ticker          : Stock ticker symbol if available (string), Treasury notes allowed (TRSN), Not null.
- asset_type      : Asset class code — "ST" (stock), "OP" (option), "OT" (other)
- transaction_type: "P" for Purchase, "S" for Sale, "E" for Exchange
- transaction_date : Date in MM-DD-YYYY format (string)
- amount_range    : Dollar threshold as a string — use the UPPER bound of the range:
                    "$1,001 - $15,000"     → "15001"
                    "$15,001 - $50,000"    → "50001"
                    "$50,001 - $100,000"   → "100001"
                    "$100,001 - $250,000"  → "250001"
                    "$250,001 - $500,000"  → "500001"
                    "$500,001 - $1,000,000"→ "1000001"
                    "$1,000,001+"          → "..."

METADATA FIELDS (include only if present in document, otherwise omit key entirely):
- shares        : Number of shares (integer | null)
- strike_price  : Strike price in USD (float | null)
- instrument    : Instrument type e.g. "call options", "put options", "common stock"

RETURN FORMAT — follow this schema exactly:
{
  "filing_id": "string",
  "first_name": "string",
  "last_name": "string",
  "middle_name": "string",
  "status": "string",
  "state_district": "string",
  "transactions": [
    {
      "asset_name": "string",
      "ticker": "string",
      "asset_type": "ST | OP | OT",
      "transaction_type": "P | S | E",
      "transaction_date": "MM-DD-YYYY",
      "amount_range": "string",
      "metadata": {
        "shares": "integer | null",
        "strike_price": "float | null",
        "instrument": "string | null"
      }
      
    }
  ],
  
}

